data.description:
**Odds and evens** is a simple game of chance and hand game, involving two people simultaneously revealing a number of fingers and winning or losing depending on whether they are odd or even. The game may be used to make a decision or played for fun.

Examples:

|         | Player 1 | Player 2 | Result |
|---------|----------|----------|--------|
| Fingers |     1    |     1    |  evens |
| Fingers |     1    |     2    |  odds  |
| Fingers |     2    |     2    |  evens |

Note: There is no chance to tie; since, if one player chooses even the other it is up to him odd and vice versa.

Known, the **Player** class determines who is the winner by completing the **whoWin** function.

class **Player** {

	protected $name;
	protected $decision;
	protected $fingers;

	public function __construct($name){
		$this->name = $name;
		$this->fingers = random_int(1,2);
	}

	public function getName()
	{
		return $this->name;
	}

	public function getFingers()
	{
		return $this->fingers;
	}

	public function getDecision()
	{
		return $this->decision;
	}
}
